  <title>Section 4.2: Good and Poor Ways to Sample</title>

  <slide>
    <title>Key Ideas</title>

    <p>
      A <term>sample survey</term> selects a <term>sample</term> of people from a population and collects data from them (observational study).
      Contrast this with a <term>census</term> which aims to collect data from every member of a population.
    </p>
    <p>
      We will learn about how sampling should occur to get good results
    </p>
